      <guid>https://nikhil-ravi.github.io/authors/admin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a Ph.D. student in Electrical Engineering at Arizona State University, working in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://scaglione.engineering.asu.edu/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;SINE lab&lt;/a&gt; under &lt;strong&gt;Professor Anna Scaglione&lt;/strong&gt;. My research is focused on dynamic multi-agent systems, in particular on developing Byzantine fault-tolerant decentralized optimization algorithms. Most recently, I have been working on distributed ledger infrastructure in Blockchain based Transactive Energy Systems; particularly focusing on ensuring Byzantine fault-tolerance in transactions over ledgers for power systems state verification.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
